fields.title: Tender Addendum: VERTU SKODA
fields.description:
Please find attached Tender Addendum No. 1 concerning the ongoing tender for P2381 Nottingham Skoda.

 

This addendum has been issued to respond to a series of Requests for Information (RFIs). The information provided is relevant to all bidders and is being shared in the interest of fairness, transparency, and consistency of tender documentation.

 

Key Notes:

  • The addendum includes responses that clarify elements of the design, scope of works, services responsibilities, and other project particulars.
  • Several referenced drawings (e.g. 8749s/04, 05, 06, 08A, 10) should be reviewed in conjunction with the responses.
  • Please ensure your pricing and proposals reflect the clarifications provided.

 

The current proposed tender return date of 9th June 2025 remains unchanged.

If any tenderer believes the issued clarifications affect their ability to return a compliant bid on time, please notify us at the earliest opportunity.

 

If you have any further queries or require clarification on any part of the information issued, please submit an RFI in the usual manner.

fields.title: Tender Addendum 10.06.25 : Flat Iron
fields.description:
The client has asked us to submit any outstanding RFI by close of business this Friday, the 13th, to ensure they have sufficient time to review and respond prior to the deadline. If you could kindly ensure that if you have any RFIs, they are sent over as soon as possible please.


Additionally, please note the following changes to the tender; (Please note that all revised drawings reflecting the changes outlined below are available via the provided link and are included under 'Tender Addendum 1 – 10.06.25').


1.)   Please find attached Drawings 3838.03(11) & 3838.03(10). These drawings contain information relating to the Lang and Fulton Italia 80 lightweight acoustic louvred metal screening on the roof. It is apparent that the bill description for this item contains the incorrect sizes. Can you please price the drawings and not the sizes contained within the bill description.


2.)   Flat Iron are keen to move away from Fixed Seating being a client direct, therefore, please ensure this element is priced.


3.)   No quantity was included for the plasterboard wall linings in Bill 2, rows 26, 30, 32, 34, 36 as none was shown on the drawing. This does not need to be priced.


4.)   The quantities for the external decorations in Bill 1 row 283 & 285 are incorrect and the drawing referenced is also incorrect. This was due to a change of drawings during the bill production stage. The correct drawing is 3838.06(19) and is included with the tender pack and also attached. Please measure this element yourself from the updated drawings or provide a cost for the works as an item. I will ensure this is normalised during the tender return stage.


5.)   With reference to the specification of the carpet included within the floor finishes section, Macaulay Sinclair have advised this does need to be priced and will instead be vinyl. Please do not price these works. The small increase to vinyl will be captured post tender.
